roduced by Sony Pictures Animation for Netflix. The companies have finalized a deal to bring out a sequel in 2029.\n\nFrom directors Maggie Kang and Chris Appelhans, â€œKPop Demon Huntersâ€ follows K-pop superstar trio Huntr/x, who when they arenâ€™t selling out stadiums use their secret identities as badass demon hunters to protect their fans from an ever-present supernatural threat. Together, they must face their biggest enemy yet: the Saja Boys, an irresistible rival boy band of demons in disguise.\n\nSEE ALSO: Hideo Kojima Talks â€˜Death Stranding 2â€™ and the Importance of Connection: â€˜Itâ€™s Not Connection With Headshots and Shooting Each Otherâ€™", "language": "en", "category": "entertainment", "source": "https://variety.com/feed/", "published": "Tue, 23 Dec 2025 14:15:40 +0000", "fetched_at": "2025-12-23T14:42:53.464241"}
{"title": "â€˜Assassinâ€™s Creedâ€™ Netflix Series to Be Directed by Johan Renck (EXCLUSIVE)", "link": "https://variety.com/2025/tv/global/assassins-creed-netflix-directed-johan-renck-1236610672/", "summary": "Netflix&#8217; upcoming live-action â€œAssassinâ€™s Creedâ€ series â€”Â which has already been building out its main cast, with Toby Wallace (&#8220;Euphoria&#8221;), Lola Petticrew (&#8220;Say Nothing&#8221;) recently unveiled as leads and Zachary Hart (&#8220;Slow Horses&#8221;) and Laura Marcus (&#8220;Death by Lightning&#8221;) as regulars â€” has now found its director. Johan Renck, the Swedish filmmaker best known for directing [&#8230;]", "content": "Netflixâ€˜ upcoming live-action â€œAssassinâ€™s Creedâ€ series â€” which has already been building out its main cast, with Toby Wallace (â€œEuphoriaâ€), Lola Petticrew (â€œSay Nothingâ€) recently unveiled as leads and Zachary Hart (â€œSlow Horsesâ€) and Laura Marcus (â€œDeath by Lightningâ€) as regulars â€” has now found its director.\n\nJohan Renck, the Swedish filmmaker best known for directing HBOâ€™s hit mini-series â€œChernobyl,â€ for which he won an Emmy, is set to helm the show, Variety can reveal.\n\nBased on the phenomenally successful time-travelling video game franchise, â€œAssassinâ€™s Creedâ€ was first announced in July as the first series to be developed under Netflixâ€™s agreement with Ubisoft, signed in 2020.\n\nPopular on Variety\n\nPlot details are being kept under wraps for now, but the logline says the series will be â€œcentered on the secret war between two shadowy factions â€” one set on determining mankindâ€™s future through control and manipulation, while the other fights to preserve free will. The series follows its characters across pivotal historical events as they battle to shape humanityâ€™s destiny.â€\n\nRoberto Patino and David Wiener serve as creators, showrunners, and executive producers. Gerard Guillemot, Margaret Boykin, Austin Dill, and Genevieve Jones of Ubisoft Film & Television serve as executive producers, as does Matt Oâ€™Toole.\n\nThe first â€œAssassinâ€™s Creedâ€ game â€” exploring the centuries long war between the rival secret orders of the Assassins and the Templar â€” debuted in 2007 and became an instant hit. Since then, 13 further installments in the franchise have been released, the most recent being â€œAssassinâ€™s Creed: Shadows,â€ released in 2025, with more than 230 million copies overall sold to date. A film adaptation starring Michael Fassbender was released in 2016.\n\nAlongside â€œChernobyl,â€ Renckâ€™s TV credits include directing the series â€œThe Last Panther,â€ plus episodes of â€œBreaking Bad,â€ â€œThe Walking Dead,â€ â€œVikings,â€ â€œBates Motelâ€ and â€œHalt and Catch Fire.â€ He has collaborated with Netflix previously, having directed the first two episodes of its 2015 series â€œBloodlineâ€ and last yearâ€™s sci-fi feature â€œSpaceman,â€ starring Adam Sandler and based on the novel â€œSpaceman of Bohemia.â€\n\nSpeaking to Variety last year ahead of the Berlinale world premiere of â€œSpaceman,â€ Renck said that after the success of 2019â€™s â€œChernobyl,â€ which was a critical and commercial smash and won numerous Emmy, Golden Globe and BAFTA TV awards, he was â€œdetermined to quitâ€ and instead wanted to open â€œreally fucking cool restaurantâ€ in Brooklyn.", "language": "en", "category": "entertainment", "source": "https://variety.com/feed/", "published": "Tue, 23 Dec 2025 10:10:20 +0000", "fetched_at": "2025-12-23T14:42:53.688354"}
{"title": "Ayushmann Khurrana Banks on Family Entertainment With Four-Film Slate Following â€˜Thammaâ€™ Success (EXCLUSIVE)", "link": "https://variety.com/2025/film/news/ayushmann-khurrana-family-entertainment-four-film-slate-1236616388/", "summary": "Bollywood star Ayushmann Khurrana is riding high on the success of &#8220;Thamma,&#8221; his first festive release that crossed the INR 100 crore mark ($11.1 million) at the box office, marking his fifth film to achieve the milestone and his biggest opener to date. The film is the latest entry in Maddock Films&#8217; horror-comedy universe. The [&#8230;]", "content": "Bollywood star Ayushmann Khurrana is riding high on the success of â€œThamma,â€ his first festive release that crossed the INR 100 crore mark ($11.1 million) at the box office, marking his fifth film to achieve the milestone and his biggest opener to date. The film is the latest entry in Maddock Filmsâ€˜ horror-comedy universe.\n\nThe actor, long known for championing realistic, slice-of-life cinema, is now pivoting toward wholesome family entertainment with a slate of four upcoming projects.\n\nâ€œThe texture of the theatricals has changed post-pandemic, and in such a scenario, this success feels hugely affirming,â€ Khurrana tells Variety. â€œMy heart is full of gratitude that both â€˜Dream Girl 2â€™ and â€˜Thammaâ€™ were successful. Iâ€™m thrilled to be entering into 2026 with two consecutive 100 crore hits.â€\n\nPopular on Variety\n\nLeading his 2026 lineup is â€œPati Patni Aur Woh Do,â€ which Khurrana describes as â€œa clean family comedy, and there is always a space for clean family comedies.â€ The film draws inspiration from the 1978 hit starring Sanjeev Kumar and is backed by BR Chopra Films, headed by Juno Chopra.\n\nKhurrana expresses particular enthusiasm for his collaboration with filmmaker Sooraj Barjatya, known for his family-oriented films. â€œFor his stature, heâ€™s a very simple man, very humble and hardworking at the same time,â€ the actor says. â€œWhat inspires me most about him is that heâ€™s a true student of cinema and works like a nerd. Iâ€™m a true fan boy of his kind of family entertainers, heâ€™s a master of this genre and there is true dearth of this genre. No one does it better than Sooraj sir.â€\n\nThe Barjatya project represents a departure from Khurranaâ€™s typical roles. â€œWhat excites me most about his film is that the hero isnâ€™t just one character, the entire family takes centre stage in his family entertainers,â€ he explains. â€œI usually enjoy playing characters who are flawed and evolve over time, but this film is different â€“ it celebrates a wholesome, ideal family as the hero.â€\n\nKhurrana will also begin filming an untitled Yash Raj Films-Posham Pa project in early 2026, followed by the release of a Dharma Productions and Sikhya Entertainment co-production â€“ a spy comedy.\n\nThe actor, known for his producer-friendly track record, emphasizes his collaborative approach. â€œWhen I commit to a project and step onto a shoot, I make it a point to keep things simple, even with my entourage,â€ Khurrana says. â€œFor me, itâ€™s not only about the scripts I choose but also about the kind of professional I am. I take pride in being a collaborator first, rather than someone who is focused solely on being seen as the leading hero.â€\n\nKhurrana has established himself as a franchise starter, having launched successful series including â€œDream Girl,â€ â€œShubh Mangal Saavdhanâ€ and â€œBadhaai Ho.â€\n\nâ€œThe credibility of its predecessor is a plus that a franchise film has,â€ he notes. â€œThe audienceâ€™s choices have become selective when it comes to venturing out and watching a new film. So, the priority is always to make a top-notch product, and it really helps when you have a successful franchise to back it.â€\n\nThe actor also expresses interest in exploring â€œAndhadhun 2â€ in the future.", "language": "en", "category": "entertainment", "source": "https://variety.com/feed/", "published": "Tue, 23 Dec 2025 07:56:26 +0000", "fetched_at": "2025-12-23T14:42:53.909665"}
{"title": "BBC To Reveal The Untold Story Of How It Tried To Persuade Laurence Olivier To Make His Debut TV Appearance", "link": "https://deadline.com/2025/12/bbc-archives-laurence-olivier-david-attenborough-vanessa-redgrave-1236655715/", "summary": "The untold story of how the BBC tried to persuade Laurence Olivier to make his first TV appearance is to be released in a new archive project from the corporation. The BBC will also publish a chain of correspondence betweenÂ the broadcaster and Vanessa Redgrave, containing a letter from 1952 when the 15-year-old aspiring actress seeks [&#8230;]", "content": "The untold story of how the BBC tried to persuade Laurence Olivier to make his first TV appearance is to be released in a new archive project from the corporation.\n\nThe BBC will also publish a chain of correspondence between the broadcaster and Vanessa Redgrave, containing a letter from 1952 when the 15-year-old aspiring actress seeks an audition for herself and her brother Corin.\n\nBoth will be contained in a new archives initiative, which will publish a tranche of 50,000 files detailing part of the 100-year-old national broadcasterâ€™s history.\n\nThere is also a letter from the BBC inviting David Attenborough to apply for the Television Training Scheme following his unsuccessful application for a producer role in 1952 â€“ a decision that arguably changed the course of broadcasting history.\n\nWatch on Deadline\n\nOlivier appeared in a number of hit ITV series like Brideshead Revisited, along with American TV including The Moon and Sixpence, but he was never in a BBC drama. This could have been different, the BBC archives reveal, with internal memos showing how the national broadcaster tried to persuade Olivier to make his debut TV appearance. Olivier is a doyen of the British screen and stage, winning an Oscar and five BAFTAs.\n\nThe BBC said the archives will also show Attenboroughâ€™s application for the TV training scheme. Attenborough is best known for his nature documentaries, for which he is unquestionably the worldâ€™s best, but he was also the second controller of BBC Two back in the 1960s. The channel thrived under his tenure and he went on to be probably its most successful presenter.\n\nThe BBC archives initiative, which will release 50,000 files, will also publish reports and cables from the 1930s and 1940s documenting President Franklin D Rooseveltâ€™s presidential inauguration and wartime broadcasts, and correspondence detailing Jawaharlal Nehruâ€™s special BBC broadcasts on Gandhi and world development.\n\nâ€œThis release is part of our plans to make more of the BBCâ€™s written archives available to the public, opening up the stories behind our programmes and people who have helped shape British broadcasting,â€ said Noreen Adams, the BBCâ€™s Director of Archives Technology & Services. â€œThis first batch includes extraordinary material with some of our biggest household names, alongside thousands of other documents that give fresh context to our cultural history.â€", "language": "en", "category": "entertainment", "source": "https://deadline.com/feed/", "published": "Tue, 23 Dec 2025 10:16:26 +0000", "fetched_at": "2025-12-23T14:42:54.338237"}
{"title": "Lizzie Avery Dies: Long-Serving NBCUniversal TV Sales Exec Was 54", "link": "https://deadline.com/2025/12/lizzie-avery-dead-nbcuniversal-tv-sales-exec-was-54-1236648693/", "summary": "Lizzie Avery, the long-serving NBCUniversal (NBCU) international TV sales exec, has died aged 54. The well-respected and much-liked Avery passed away unexpectedly earlier this month, her family said. She had spent nearly 24 years with Comcast-owned NBCU, rising from a sales administration manager role to eventually become SVP &#38; EMEA Lead Sales Liaison for TV [&#8230;]", "content": "Lizzie Avery, the long-serving NBCUniversal (NBCU) international TV sales exec, has died aged 54.\n\nThe well-respected and much-liked Avery passed away unexpectedly earlier this month, her family said. She had spent nearly 24 years with Comcast-owned NBCU, rising from a sales administration manager role to eventually become SVP & EMEA Lead Sales Liaison for TV distribution.\n\nFor the past three years, Avery had led a regional sales team of 30 in EMEA.\n\nâ€œIt is with great sadness that we share the heartbreaking news that Lizzie Avery, SVP & EMEA Sales Lead for TVD, passed away unexpectedly yesterday,â€ wrote NBCUâ€™s President of Global TV Distribution, Michael Bonner, and EVP, Sales Liaison, International, Carolyn Stalins in a note to staff on December 8.\n\nThey called her a â€œdeeply valued memberâ€ of the NBCU team, adding: â€œHer leadership, energy and warmth touched all of us, and her loss is immeasurable.â€\n\nWatch on Deadline\n\nCoincidentially, L.A.-based Stalins had this month been in London, where NBCU offered on-site counselling for staff members â€“ a sign of stature in which the international executive was held within the company.\n\nAvery had begun her career in theatrical sales for 20th Century Fox before a short spell at Disney. She joined NBCU in the early 2000s and began her climb through the ranks.\n\nHer former boss at NBCU, Don McGregor, who is currently a consultant for Paramount and soon to join the Skydance-owned company full-time in the new year, was close friends with Avery. â€œLizzie and I began working together at NBCUâ€™s London office in 2002,â€ he said. â€œShe quickly rose through the ranks as a sales leader, friend and mentor to the many lucky people who had the privilege of working with her. I genuinely believe there is no one like her in the world; she was a wonderful human being who made you strive to be a better person.\n\nâ€œOur business was so fortunate to have her as part of our community. The way she balanced being professional and confident in her negotiations while remaining personable and funny â€“ not only as a genuine friend, but also as a colleague â€“ made every interaction meaningful and important. Lizzie not only loved her beautiful family but also treasured her clients and colleagues tremendously. She will be deeply missed and will forever make an impact on the many people who knew her.â€\n\nMcGregorâ€™s sentiment was shared by many international acquisitions industry, and Deadline has heard from several expressing their sadness, even those on the other side of the negotiating table.\n\nSue Deeks, Head of Scripted Pre-Buy Acquisitions at the BBC, said: â€œI feel so very fortunate to have known Lizzie. Not only was she an absolute pleasure to deal with professionally, she was also one of the nicest people you could ever hope to meet â€“ kind-hearted, fun to be with, just a really lovely person. Her team simply adored her, and you could see why. Lizzieâ€™s loss to all her many friends in the business is immeasurable. We will all miss her so very, very much.â€\n\n\n\nâ€œI was lucky enough to have known Lizzie for over 20 years,â€ added Katie Keenan, Group Director of Acquisitions at Sky. â€œWe came up in our careers together and often spoke about how we juggled our professional and personal lives â€“ she was always a wise and steady counsel. It was a privilege to sit on the other side of the negotiating table from her â€“ Lizzie always brought her A-game with grace, composure, and quiet strength. She loved her work and cared deeply for her people; I know her legacy will endure with the amazing team she built at NBCUâ€™s GTVD.â€\n\nAvery is survived by her husband and two children.", "language": "en", "category": "entertainment", "source": "https://deadline.com/feed/", "published": "Tue, 23 Dec 2025 09:00:00 +0000", "fetched_at": "2025-12-23T14:42:54.661176"}
{"title": "Taylor Swift Teases More Music To Come After â€˜The Life Of A Showgirlâ€™ In â€˜The End Of An Eraâ€™ Docuseries", "link": "https://deadline.com/2025/12/taylor-swift-teases-new-music-end-of-an-era-docuseries-1236655659/", "summary": "Taylor Swift has made it clear once again that she has no intentions to stop writing and releasing new music. The pop star cheekily teases that new music will eventually be on the way in the final moments of her The End of an Era docuseries. The six-episode series concludes by listing out a few [&#8230;]", "content": "Taylor Swift has made it clear once again that she has no intentions to stop writing and releasing new music.\n\nThe pop star cheekily teases that new music will eventually be on the way in the final moments of her The End of an Era docuseries. The six-episode series concludes by listing out a few of the milestones sheâ€™s reached since the Eras Tour ended on December 8, 2024, including buying back her first six albums and getting engaged to Travis Kelce.\n\nThen, it notes that she released a new album, The Life of a Showgirl, on October 3, and it became â€œthe biggest album of her career.â€ A brief moment later, the words â€œto dateâ€ pop up underneath. The sly addition hints that her 12th studio album will not be her last and that there will be more to come.\n\nSwift previously shut down speculation that Showgirl might be her final album, saying during an interview on BBC Radio 2 just after its release that assuming she would stop producing music to focus on her personal life was â€œshockingly offensive.â€\n\nWatch on Deadline\n\nâ€œItâ€™s not why people get married, so they can quit their job,â€ she said, adding in regard to her fans: â€œOh, I know they love to panic sometimes, but itâ€™s like I love the person that I am with because he loves what I do and he loves how much I am fulfilled by making art and making music.â€\n\nShe continued: â€œThatâ€™s the coolest thing about Travis, like he is so passionate about what he does, that me being passionate about what I do, it connects us. Thereâ€™s no point in time where heâ€™s gonna be like, â€˜Iâ€™m really upset that youâ€™re still making the music.'â€\n\nThe End of an Era gives fans a behind-the-scenes look at the last legs of Swiftâ€™s record-breaking Eras Tour in Europe and North America. The Eras Tour is the highest-grossing tour of all time, raking in $2.2B while spanning 149 shows across 21 countries and breaking numerous stadium attendance records.\n\nIn the final episode, Swift savors the final three shows in Vancouver and counts down to closing the book on yet another era of her life with her family and crew.", "language": "en", "category": "entertainment", "source": "https://deadline.com/feed/", "published": "Tue, 23 Dec 2025 08:05:00 +0000", "fetched_at": "2025-12-23T14:42:54.953431"}
{"title": "Democratic Congresswoman Sues To Remove Donald Trump From Kennedy Centerâ€™s Name", "link": "https://deadline.com/2025/12/trump-kennedy-center-lawsuit-name-1236655635/", "summary": "A congresswoman who is an ex officio member of the Kennedy Center board sued other trustees on Monday, seeking a court ruling to force them to remove Donald Trump from the name of the arts institution. Rep. Joyce Beatty (D-OH) filed the lawsuit on Monday in federal court in Washington, D.C., seeking a declaration that [&#8230;]", "content": "A congresswoman who is an ex officio member of the Kennedy Center board sued other trustees on Monday, seeking a court ruling to force them to remove Donald Trump from the name of the arts institution.\n\nRep. Joyce Beatty (D-OH) filed the lawsuit on Monday in federal court in Washington, D.C., seeking a declaration that the name of the arts institution is the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts, and that a board vote last week to change the name is null and void.\n\nâ€œBecause Congress named the center by statute, changing the Kennedy Centerâ€™s name requires an act of Congress,â€ Beattyâ€™s lawsuit stated. â€œBut on December 18 and 19, 2025â€”in scenes more reminiscent of authoritarian regimes than the American republicâ€”the sitting President and his handpicked loyalists renamed this storied center after President Trump. This is a flagrant violation of the rule of law, and it flies in the face of our constitutional order. Congress intended the Center to be a living memorial to President Kennedyâ€”and a crown jewel of the arts for all Americans, irrespective of party. Unless and until this Court intervenes, Defendants will continue to defy Congress and thwart the law for improper ends.â€\n\nThe Trump controlled board voted to rename the center on Thursday. The next day, workers added Trumpâ€™s name to the facade of the complex, so it reads â€œThe Donald Trump and The John F. Kennedy Memorial Center for the Performing Arts.â€\n\nWatch on Deadline\n\nThe lawsuit named Trump, who is chairman of the Kennedy Center, as well as its president, Ric Grenell, and the members of the board, along with the institution itself. Also named are other ex officio members, including Secretary of Health and Human Services Robert Kennedy Jr., House Speaker Mike Johnson and Senate Majority Leader John Thune.\n\nThe lawsuit cited breach of trustees obligations under federal law and violation of plaintiffâ€™s rights under federal law, among other claims.\n\nBeatty also is seeking an order that â€œany and all physical and digital signage purporting to\n\nrename the Kennedy Center after Defendant Trump, including the signage on the buildingâ€™s\n\nfront portico and the website.â€\n\nThe center did not immediately respond to a request for comment on Beattyâ€™s lawsuit.\n\nPresident Lyndon Johnson signed a law in 1964 designating the National Cultural Center as the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts. After the Trump-controlled board voted, Democrats and members of the Kennedy family quickly cried foul.\n\nThe lawsuit called the board vote a â€œsham.â€\n\nâ€œThe conduct in the Board meeting itself confirmed that the meeting was a sham, orchestrated by Defendant Trump and his loyalists as a pretext for a predetermined result,â€ Beattyâ€™s lawsuit stated. â€œThere was no advance notice in the agenda that the Board would be considering a name change. The meeting was held at the home of Andrea Wynn, the wife of a casino mogul and Republican donor, whom Defendant Trump installed on the Board. At the end of the meeting, Defendant Trumpâ€™s loyalists abruptly announced that they had news they would like to share: the Kennedy Center would now be renamed after Donald Trump.â€\n\nBeatty was on the board meeting call, but was blocked from expressing her concerns because she was put on mute, according to the lawsuit. A spokesperson for the Kennedy Center later said that ex officio members do not have a vote, something codified in the centerâ€™s bylaws.\n\nBut Beattyâ€™s lawsuit contended that the â€œlaw does not distinguish between the ex officio trustees and general trustees, and the former possess the same rights and responsibilities as the latter.â€\n\nRoma Daravi, spokeswoman for the center, defended the boardâ€™s authority to change the name. â€œThis action is in line with the precedent of the State Department adding President Trumpâ€™s name to the Institute of Peace. And the previous Administration renaming military bases,â€ she said in a statement last week. Yet the effort to strip military bases of Confederate names was authorized by an act of Congress in 2021, something that critics of the Kennedy Center renaming say is required.\n\nThe lawsuit also contended that the â€œpurported name change will impose financial and operational harms on this already struggling institution by alienating ticket holders, donors, and artists.â€ The lawsuit noted that after the name change, musician Kristy Lee announced that she was canceling her Jan. 14, 2026 performance. â€œOn information and belief, ticket holders have canceled their tickets in protest of Defendantsâ€™ unlawful actions and demanded refunds. There is every reason to expect this trend will continue, with associated financial and reputational harms,â€ the lawsuit stated.\n\nBeatty is represented by Norman Eisen, founder of Democracy Defenders Action, and Nathaniel Zelinsky, senior counsel at Washington Litigation Group.", "language": "en", "category": "entertainment", "source": "https://deadline.com/feed/", "published": "Tue, 23 Dec 2025 02:50:25 +0000", "fetched_at": "2025-12-23T14:42:55.164916"}
{"title": "TV Show Book Adaptations Arriving In 2026 So Far", "link": "https://deadline.com/feature/tv-show-based-on-books-this-year-1236035246/", "summary": "Several best-selling books will make way for returning TV shows and new ones in 2026. One of the first major arrivals in January will be A Knight of the Seven Kingdoms, based on George R. R. Martin&#8217;s The Hedge Knight. The prequel series to Game of Thrones has been a long time in the making. [&#8230;]", "content": "Several best-selling books will make way for returning TV shows and new ones in 2026.\n\nOne of the first major arrivals in January will be A Knight of the Seven Kingdoms, based on George R. R. Martinâ€™s The Hedge Knight. The prequel series to Game of Thrones has been a long time in the making. Then comes Bridgerton Season 4, based on the third book in Julia Quinnâ€™s series.\n\nMarch will see the arrival of a rarer type of book adaptation â€” the second season of The Last Thing He Told Me based on a concurrent sequel novel that Laura Dave wrote to her first book of the same name that inspired the Apple TV series. And April will welcome Margoâ€™s Got Money Troubles to the Apple TV series family.\n\nRead on for more TV shows based on books coming out this year.\n\nWatch on Deadline\n\nA Knight of the Seven Kingdoms â€“ HBO Max, Based on George R. R. Martinâ€™s The Hedge Knight\n\nL-R: Peter Claffey and Tanzyn Crawford in â€˜A Knight of the Seven Kingdomsâ€™ HBO Max\n\nA Knight of the Seven Kingdoms, which spans six episodes, is based on George R. R. Martinâ€™s prequel novella that is set in the world of A Song of Ice and Fire â€” which lent itself to House of the Dragon. The series premieres January 18.\n\nBridgerton Season 4 â€“ Netflix, Based on Julia Quinnâ€™s An Offer From A Gentleman\n\nYerin Ha as Sophie Baek in â€˜Bridgertonâ€™ Season 4 Liam Daniel/Netflix\n\nBenedict (Luke Thompson) and Sophieâ€™s (Yerin Ha) love story will take center stage after Penelope Featherington (Nicola Coughlan) and Colin Bridgerton (Luke Newton) went from friends to lovers in Season 3. Season 4 will get the split treatment just as Season 3 did, with Part 1 debuting Jan. 29 on Netflix followed by Part 2 Feb. 26.\n\nRELATED: â€˜Bridgertonâ€™ Season 4: Everything We Know So Far\n\nThe Last Thing He Told Me Season 2 â€“ Apple TV, Based on The First Time I Saw Him by Laura Dave\n\nL-R: Jennifer Garner in and Judy Greer in â€˜The Last Thing He Told Meâ€™ Season 2 Apple TV\n\nThe Last Thing He Told Me Season 2 arrives on Apple TV Feb. 20. The showâ€™s second season will take its lead from Laura Daveâ€™s new sequel novel, The First Time I Saw Him, which publishes Jan. 6, giving readers and watchers plenty of time to catch up ahead of premiere. Judy Greer has joined Season 2, as have Rita Wilson and more.\n\nRELATED: Jennifer Garner On â€˜The Last Thing He Told Meâ€™: â€œI Didnâ€™t Think I Could Survive If Somebody Else Played The Roleâ€; Author Laura Dave Hints Season 2 â€“ Contenders TV\n\nOutlander, Season 8 â€“ STARZ, Based on Diana Gabaldon\n\nThe final season of STARZâ€™s Outlander arrives in March. The show is based on Diana Gabaldonâ€™s hugely popular historical fantasy series that spans nine novels and two novellas.\n\nScarpetta â€“ Prime Video, Based on Patricia Cornwellâ€™s Book Series\n\nKay Scarpetta (Nicole Kidman) Prime Video\n\nPrime Videoâ€™s Nicole Kidman-starring Scarpetta landed a two-season order at the streamer. Kidman will star as the titular Kay Scarpetta, a medical examiner whose attention to detail and steady hand allow her to speak up for victims and unmask a serial killer.\n\nMargoâ€™s Got Money Troubles â€“ Apple TV, Based on Rufi Thorpeâ€™s Novel of the Same Name\n\nMichelle Pfeiffer (standing) and Elle Fanning (lying down) in â€˜Margoâ€™s Got Money Troublesâ€™ Apple TV\n\nElle Fanning stars as Margo, a single mom who dropped out of college to raise her child and found a new source of income in the process â€” OnlyFans. In the Apple TV show based on Rufi Thorpeâ€™s best-selling novel, Michelle Pfeiffer stars as Margoâ€™s mother Shyanne, and Nick Offerman will portray her father, former professional wrestler, Jinx. The star-studded cast doesnâ€™t stop there. Margoâ€™s Got Money Troubles debuts April 15.\n\nReturning and New Book-to-TV Adaptations in the Works:\n\nBelow find a list of book adaptations in progress from early stages such as casting to production:\n\nAdaptations From 2025:\n\nFind some of the big book-to-series adaptations of 2025 below.\n\nLong Bright River â€“ Peacock â€“ March\n\nLONG BRIGHT RIVER â€” â€œThese Girlsâ€ Episode 101 â€” Pictured: (l-r) Amanda Seyfried as Mickey, Ashleigh Cummings as Casey â€” (PEACOCK) Peacock\n\nBased on the best-selling book by Liz Moore, Long Bright Riverâ€™s television adaptation arrived on Peacock in March. The show stars Amanda Seyfried in the role of Michaela â€œMickeyâ€ Fitzpatrick.\n\nRansom Canyon â€“ Netflix â€“ April\n\nL-R: Josh Duhamel as Staten and Minka Kelly as Quinn in â€˜Ransom Canyonâ€™ on Netflix Anna Kooris/Netflix\n\nRansom Canyon by Jodi Thomas was adapted into a ten-episode season of television that is now streaming on Netflix. Starring Josh Duhamel and Minka Kelley, the show also follows two other romances in the small Texas town, with the addition of a murder mystery â€œspineâ€ as showrunnger and creator April Blair called the element of investigating the death of Duhamelâ€™s rancher Staten Kirklandâ€™s son.\n\nForever by Judy Blume â€“ Netflix â€“ May 8\n\nLovie Simone, Michael Cooper Jr. in â€˜Foreverâ€™ Elizabeth Morris / Â©Netflix / Courtesy Everett Collection\n\nJudy Blumeâ€™s Forever, published 50 years ago, has been reimagined by producer, creator and showrunner Mara Brock Akil. The show stars Lovie Simone as Keisha Clark and Michael Cooper Jr. as Justin Edwards, a respective up and coming track and field star with good grades and a basketball player whoâ€™s really a nerd in an athleteâ€™s body. The pairâ€™s flame that kindles throughout the show reflects the strong feelings of first love that many teenagers experience.\n\nWe Were Liars by E. Lockhart â€“ Season 1 on Prime Video â€“ June 18\n\nEmily Alyn Lind, Esther McGregor, Joseph Zada and Subham Maheshwar in â€˜We Were Liarsâ€™ Prime Video\n\nApple TV+â€™s adaptation of Hugh Howeyâ€™s novels will return with a Season 2 in November. The show stars Rebecca Ferguson, Common, Harriet Walter, Chinza Uche, Avi Nash, Alexandria Riley, Shane McRae, Remmie Milner, Clare Perkins, Billy Postlethwaite, Rick Gomez, Caitlin Zoz, Tanya Moodie and Iain Glen. with Steve Zahn joining the cast for Season 2.\n\nThe Buccaneers by Edith Wharton â€“ Apple TV+ â€“ June 18, 2025\n\nSeason 2 of Apple TV+â€™s The Buccaneers will arrive this summer, and Leighton Meester has joined the cast. Based on the book by Edith Wharton, which was published with multiple versions that end differently, the showâ€™s first season followed a group of five girls led by Nan (Kristine FrÃ¸seth) who venture to England from their American homes during the Gilded Age, exemplifying the culture clash between the two countries.\n\nThe Summer I Turned Pretty Season 3 (Weâ€™ll Always Have Summer by Jenny Han) â€“ Prime Video â€“ July 16\n\nThe third and final season of Prime Videoâ€™s The Summer I Turned Pretty is slated to come out July 16 with a bonus amount of episodes to bring the adaptation of Jenny Hanâ€™s beloved book trilogy to a conclusion. The third installment of the YA coming-of-age series, based in Weâ€™ll Always Have Summer, will unfold in a whopping 11 episodes, one of which will be directed by Han. Season 1 had seven episodes, which all dropped on the streamer at once, and Season 2 had eight, which released week to week after the first three rolled out on premiere day.\n\nRELATED: â€˜The Summer I Turned Prettyâ€™ Movie Greenlit At Prime Video\n\nWashington Black by Esi Edugyan â€“ Hulu â€“ July 23\n\nL-R: Sharon Duncan-Brewster and Sterling K. Brown in â€˜Washington Blackâ€™ Chris Reardon/Disney\n\nWashington Black will follow the 19th-century journey of George Washington â€œWashâ€ Black, an 11-year-old boy born on a sugar plantation in Barbados. Washâ€™s scientific skill and genius set him up for an interesting and unexpected destiny. Forced to flee his home, he sets out on an expedition across the globe, encountering all kinds of people and characters. The series will star Ernest Kingsley Jr. as Washington Black, Ruper Graves as Mr. Goff, Iola Evans as Tanna Goff, Edward Bluemel as William McGee, Sharon Duncan Brewster as Miss Angie, Eddie Karanga as Young Washington Black, Tom Ellis as Tith and Sterling K. Brown as Medwin.\n\nMy Life With the Walter Boys by Ali Novak â€“ Season 2, Netflix, August\n\n(L to R) Ashby Gentry as Alex, Noah LaLonde as Cole in â€˜My Life with the Walter Boysâ€™ Season 2 David Brown/Netflix\n\nAfter a popular first season on Netflix adapted from Ali Novakâ€™s novel that gained traction on Wattpad, My Life With the Walter Boys will is in the midst of production on a second season, though the first season did tackle all the book material. Novak is writing another Walter Boys novel called My Return to the Walter Boys, but the showâ€™s second season wonâ€™t be connected with that book.\n\nAll Her Fault â€“ Peacock â€“ Nov. 6, Based on Andrea Maraâ€™s Novel\n\nPeacockâ€™s strong hit series All Her Fault, starring Sarah Snook, Dakota Fanning and Jake Lacy among others, arrived on the streamer at the beginning of November. The story follows Marissa (Snook), whose son goes missing after a playdate. When Snookâ€™s character shows up to pick up her son Milo (Duke McCloud), she doesnâ€™t recognize the lady at the front door, and the woman doesnâ€™t have Milo.\n\nPercy Jackson and the Olympians Season 2 (The Sea of Monsters) â€“ December 10\n\nPercy Jackson and the Olympians on Disney+ Disney+\n\nRick Riordanâ€™s Percy Jackson and the Olympians series Season 2 will be based on the events found in the second book of the original quintet: The Sea of Monsters. Season 2 of the Greek mythology-grounded fictional series will arrive on Disney+ in 2025. New casting additions that have been made ahead of the continuation of Percy, Grover and Annabethâ€™s story include Daniel Diemer as Percyâ€™s half-brother Tyson, a Cyclops, Tamara Smart as Thalia Grace, daughter of Zeus, Andra Day as Annabethâ€™s mother the goddess Athena and Courtney B. Vance as the god of skies and thunder, Zeus. Vance will take over from the late Lance Reddick who died shortly after the release of the first season.\n\nThank the gods, Disney renewed the Greek mythology-based YA series for a third season, which will likely follow the events of Riordanâ€™s The Titanâ€™s Curse, ahead of the Season 2 premiere on Disney+.", "language": "en", "category": "entertainment", "source": "https://deadline.com/feed/", "published": "Tue, 23 Dec 2025 02:35:15 +0000", "fetched_at": "2025-12-23T14:42:55.477146"}
{"title": "Lily Collins Premieres â€˜Emily in Parisâ€™ Season 5, Connor Storrie and FranÃ§ois Arnaud Walk the â€˜Is This Thing On?â€™ Red Carpet and More Celeb Photos From December 2025", "link": "https://variety.com/gallery/celebrity-photos-red-carpet-december-2025/", "summary": "Hollywood returned from the Thanksgiving holiday and headed to New York City to kick off December with the star-studded Gotham Awards. Paul Thomas Andersonâ€™s â€œOne Battle After Anotherâ€ picked up the top prize of best feature, while Jafar Panahi&#8217;s &#8220;It Was Just an Accident&#8221; picked up three statuettes. In London, Cate Blanchett, Lily Allen and [&#8230;]", "content": "Hollywood returned from the Thanksgiving holiday and headed to New York City to kick off December with the star-studded Gotham Awards. Paul Thomas Andersonâ€™s â€œOne Battle After Anotherâ€ picked up the top prize of best feature, while Jafar Panahiâ€™s â€œIt Was Just an Accidentâ€ picked up three statuettes.\n\nIn London, Cate Blanchett, Lily Allen and Sharon Stone appeared at The Fashion Awards at Royal Albert Hall.\n\nThe following night, Sydney Sweeney and Amanda Seyfried stunned on the red carpet at the premiere of their new Paul Feig thriller, â€œThe Housemaid.â€\n\nAt the same time, Ariana Grande and Cynthia Erivo wowed at a Los Angeles reception for â€œWicked: For Goodâ€ with performance of â€œFor Goodâ€ and the Barbra Streisand and Judy Garland-inspired medley of â€œHappy Days Are Here Againâ€ and â€œGet Happy.â€ Baz Luhrmann flew in from Japan to host the evening with Colleen Camp.\n\nâ€œLook, itâ€™s easy to come from Tokyo and do this because itâ€™s so hard to make a live-action musical,â€ Luhrmann said. He praised director Jon M. Chu for making films that â€œcan touch the youngest audience member, an older audience member and be both incredible classical but so pop â€¦ that are so about inclusiveness, so about what brings us together [and] not what pushes us apart.â€\n\nMake sure to keep check back all month long for more red carpet photos from December 2025.", "language": "en", "category": "entertainment", "source": "https://variety.com/feed/", "published": "Tue, 23 Dec 2025 14:30:35 +0000", "fetched_at": "2025-12-23T14:56:41.308094"}
{"title": "â€˜Agonâ€™ Director Giulio Bertelli on How He Got Mubi To Board His Offbeat Allegorical Drama on Sports, Technology, and War", "link": "https://variety.com/2025/film/global/agon-giulio-bertelli-mubi-offbeat-drama-sports-technology-1236616455/", "summary": "First-time Italian director Giulio Bertelli, who is fashion designer Miuccia Pradaâ€™s son, made what is probably this year&#8217;s most offbeat Italian feature film debut with â€œAgon,â€ an allegorical drama that follows three female athletes competing in judo, fencing and target shooting within a fictional live-streamed global sports tournament called the Ludoj 2024 Games. &#8220;Agon&#8221; (which [&#8230;]", "content": "First-time Italian director Giulio Bertelli, who is fashion designer Miuccia Pradaâ€™s son, made what is probably this yearâ€™s most offbeat Italian feature film debut with â€œAgon,â€ an allegorical drama that follows three female athletes competing in judo, fencing and target shooting within a fictional live-streamed global sports tournament called the Ludoj 2024 Games.\n\nâ€œAgonâ€ (which takes its title from the Ancient Greek word for a struggle, contest or competition) was inspired by the historical figures of Joan of Arc, Cleopatra and a Russian cavalry officer called Nadezhda Durova. The experimental drama examines the social pressures of competitive sports, the use of technology and social media applied to sports, and the link between sports and war, providing a fresh and realistic look at contemporary athletic agonism.\n\nThe film stars Italian judo athlete and Olympic Gold medalist Alice Bellandi and â€œLa Chimeraâ€ stars Yile Vianello and Sofija Zobina.\n\nPopular on Variety\n\nFollowing its premiere in the Venice Film Festivalâ€™s Criticsâ€™ Week in September, â€œAgonâ€ was released in Italian cinemas, kicking off Mubiâ€™s Italian theatrical release slate, and has travelled widely on the festival circuit including the Rio, Thessaloniki, Geneva, and Brisbane fests.\n\nBertelli speaks to Variety about his personal connection to the filmâ€™s subject matter and how he brought Mubi and The Match Factory on board as producer, Italian theatrical distributor, and global distributor.\n\nYouâ€™ve been involved with the Italian sailing team that competed in the Americaâ€™s Cup. Is that what prompted you to depict the world of highly competitive sports?\n\nYes, I definitely have a personal connection to this film. But there is also a broader context. Itâ€™s true that â€œAgonâ€ is centred around the world of sports. And of course itâ€™s open to interpretations. But I also use the sports world backdrop of these fictional Olympics that are almost a geopolitical platform, to make a reflection on the role that competitive sports have taken on over the past century. And also to talk more in general about the feeling in life of not being able to achieve oneâ€™s goal. So, at one level itâ€™s also the story of three teenagers who are unable to do what they want. This is observed very differently with respect to each character, â€‹â€‹contextualising this journey in the preparation for competition in a minor sports category of a hypothetical Olympics. Then thereâ€™s the broader issue of macro connections between how we came to call sports what they are today. Where does that comes from? And the relationship between war, violence, and sports.\n\nTalk to me about your decision to cast real life world champion judo athlete Alice Bellandi in the film.\n\nI initially conceived â€œAgonâ€ as an animation project. Then, when I decided to make it live-action, I had two big problems. One was: how do I give it a realistic flavour that establishes trust with the audience? For fencing, I knew I could use a stunt person because in fencing you wear a mask. With shooting, I also knew that it was not a big problem because the athlete has to be very still. But when it comes to judo, I knew I had to find a real judoka. Then reality surpassed my expectations when I met Bellandi, who agreed to be in the film. Then five months after we shot she won the Olympic gold medal in Paris.\n\nIn simplistic terms, â€œAgonâ€ explores the relationship between sports and technology, which is very clear in competitive sailing. Talk to me about how you weaved this into the filmâ€™s narrative.\n\nIâ€™m interested in the relationship between sports and technology, but in a broader sense, which is what I think Iâ€™ll continue to look at in the future. What really interests me is the rapport between the organic world and technology, â€œorganicâ€ pertaining to the body in this movie. One example is the surgery [scene] in the film, which is obviously a very crude scene. For me itâ€™s very important because itâ€™s not a metaphor. There are other directors who have addressed this theme [of technology and the body] using metaphorical devices that have shaped my imagination. But Iâ€™m fascinated by looking at this [rapport] where it doesnâ€™t exist as a metaphor, but exists purely as reality: a robot that digs into the flesh, into the blood.\n\nTalk to me about your relationship with Mubi. How did you bring them on board in such a big way?\n\nActually, Mubi was involved in â€œAgonâ€ since the beginning, before anyone else. When I wrote this story as an animation project, I wasnâ€™t actually actively trying to get this film off the ground. I met Efe Cackarel in 2017 when Mubi was much smaller than it is now. We talked about it. I mentioned that I had this story in mind and Iâ€™d like to maybe make movies in the future. He said: â€œIâ€™m interested. Iâ€™m also interested in starting to produce in the future and not just be a platform. Why donâ€™t you write the screenplay?â€ So I wrote the screenplay and started talking about it directly with Mubi. At first we started developing it directly in London as an animation film, but then we realised that it would be too expensive and complex to do it as an animation project.\n\nMeanwhile, my life was changing. I thought: â€œmaybe this could actually be my first feature film. And Efe, rightly, said to me: â€œLook, you need you to find a producer to take this project forward. But we are on board.â€ So, with [Italian producer] Max Brun, I introduced myself to Jules Daley, who had just come out of RSA Films. She loved the project and decided to help me and become my producer on this film. So, little by little, â€œAgonâ€ was born. Then, when the project began to take shape, Mubi came on board. From the very beginning, there was the idea that they would distribute it. But they also became an equity investor. At that point, Mubi had acquired, or was in the process of acquiring, The Match Factory. So, to my great joy, I found myself working with The Match Factory as an international sales agent. Then they said: â€œInstead of selling the project, weâ€™ll distribute it directly in Italy, because they wanted to start distributing in Italy.â€\n\nThis interview has been edited and condensed for clarity.", "language": "en", "category": "entertainment", "source": "https://variety.com/feed/", "published": "Tue, 23 Dec 2025 15:15:22 +0000", "fetched_at": "2025-12-23T15:30:56.043423"}
{"title": "Chris Evans Returns for â€˜Avengers: Doomsdayâ€™ as Captain America With a Child, Teaser Confirms", "link": "https://variety.com/2025/film/news/chris-evans-avengers-doomsday-teaser-captain-america-1236609054/", "summary": "Cap is back &#8212; and he&#8217;s a dad! Marvel Studios has finally dropped the first teaser trailer for &#8220;Avengers: Doomsday&#8221; online, after it aired in theaters last Thursday attached to initial screenings of &#8220;Avatar: Fire and Ash.&#8221; The first teaser trailer has revealed that Steve Rogers, the star-spangled Avenger portrayed by Chris Evans, will return [&#8230;]", "content": "Cap is back â€” and heâ€™s a dad!\n\nMarvel Studios has finally dropped the first teaser trailer for â€œAvengers: Doomsdayâ€ online, after it aired in theaters last Thursday attached to initial screenings of â€œAvatar: Fire and Ash.â€\n\nThe first teaser trailer has revealed that Steve Rogers, the star-spangled Avenger portrayed by Chris Evans, will return in the next Marvel team-up adventure, set to release Dec. 18, 2026. In a twist, Captain America is the father to a newborn child.\n\nMarvel is slowly building up to â€œDoomsday,â€ which hits theaters in a little less than a year. There will reportedly be more teasers that focus on other characters in the coming weeks. The Captain America trailer leaked online in the run-up to its theatrical debut, and a Thor-focused teaser also appeared in social media leaks this week. Itâ€™s expected that it too will run in theaters with showings of â€œAvatar: Fire and Ashâ€ beginning Thursday, like the Cap teaser.\n\nPopular on Variety\n\nJoe and Anthony Russo, who previously directed â€œCaptain America: Winter Soldier,â€ â€œCaptain America: Civil War,â€ â€œAvengers: Infinity Warâ€ and â€œAvengers: Endgameâ€ and are back for â€œDoomsday,â€ released a short statement on their Instagram page.\n\nâ€œThe character that changed our lives,â€ they wrote of Captain America. â€œThe story that brought us all here together. It was always going to come back to thisâ€¦â€\n\nThe teaser, set on a peaceful farm, begins with Steve riding a motorcycle up to his home as a piano rendition of the â€œAvengersâ€ theme plays in the background. His blue helmet is reminiscent of his Captain America costume, which he pulls out to reminiscently admire. He holds a newborn baby and looks proudly, as the teaser ends with â€œSteve Rogers will return for â€˜Avengers: Doomsday.'â€ A countdown timer begins at the end thatâ€™s set to expire when â€œDoomsdayâ€ hits theaters.\n\nMarvel fans last saw Captain America, the founding Avenger, in the closing moments of 2019â€™s â€œAvengers: Endgame.â€ After saving the world from the purple villain known as Thanos, Cap makes it his personal mission to return the missing Infinity Stones to their rightful places across time. After finishing his time-traveling mission, an elderly Steve returns to the main MCU timeline and passes down his red-and-white Vibranium shield to his former sidekick, Sam Wilson (Anthony Mackie), upgrading him from the Falcon to the new Captain America. After bestowing his shield to Sam, Steve then goes back in time to reunite with his beloved Peggy Carter (Hayley Atwell).\n\nAfter Steve went missing and was frozen in the ice in the original â€œCaptain Americaâ€ movie, Peggy grew old but never stopped loving him. Now with the Quantum Realm time-traveling technology, the two were able to get married and live out their lives together through the decades.\n\nDoes this teaser mean that Steve somehow returns to the main MCU timeline to rejoin the Avengers? Is this the same Cap, or is he a variant of the elderly hero from the finale of â€œEndgameâ€? And whoâ€™s the baby. Does he or she have super-soldier powers like Cap?\n\nMarvel also dropped the first poster for â€œDoomsday,â€ tinged in a green hue very similar to the colors of Doctor Doomâ€™s famous costume.\n\nTechnically, this isnâ€™t Evansâ€™ first time back in the MCU since â€œEndgame.â€ In 2024â€™s billion-dollar smash â€œDeadpool & Wolverine,â€ he returned for a hilarious cameo as the Human Torch, his original superhero role way back in Foxâ€™s â€œFantastic Fourâ€ movie from 2005.\n\nIn an Esquire profile of Mackie from earlier this year, ahead of the former Falcon taking on the Cap mantle in â€œCaptain America: Brave New World,â€ Evans said that he was â€œhappily retiredâ€ and denied reports that he would return to Marvel.\n\nâ€œThatâ€™s not true,â€ Evans said about his rumored return at the time, explaining that these reports â€œhappen every couple yearsâ€ since he bowed out in â€œEndgame.â€\n\nâ€œIâ€™ve just stopped responding to it,â€ he added. â€œYeah, no â€” happily retired!â€\n\nEvans isnâ€™t the only original â€œAvengersâ€ star who will be back for â€œDoomsday.â€ Robert Downey Jr. is returning, but not as Tony Stark. Instead, he is replacing his Iron Man armor to play the ultimate villain, Doctor Doom, in the multiverse-crossing movie. Other returning heroes include Chris Hemsworth as Thor, Mackie, Danny Ramirez, Sebastian Stan, Paul Rudd, Tom Hiddleston, Letitia Wright, Winston Duke, Simu Liu, Pedro Pascal, Vanessa Kirby, Joseph Quinn, Ebon Moss-Bachrach, Florence Pugh, David Harbour, Wyatt Russell, Hannah John-Kamen and Lewis Pullman. From the â€œX-Menâ€ universe, Patrick Stewart, Ian McKellen, Kelsey Grammer, Alan Cumming, James Marsden, Channing Tatum and Rebecca Romijn will cross over into the MCU.", "language": "en", "category": "entertainment", "source": "https://variety.com/feed/", "published": "Tue, 23 Dec 2025 15:05:54 +0000", "fetched_at": "2025-12-23T15:30:56.343361"}
